{"title_page": "Laura Su\u00e1rez (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Laura Su\u00e1rez\n| image          =\n| fullname       = Laura Su\u00e1rez Ayala<ref name=SW>{{Soccerway\n| id             = 216326\n| accessdate     = 8 April 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1993|12|9|df=y}}<ref name=SW/>\n| birth_place    = Puerto Rico<ref name=GSA>{{Cite web\n| url            = https://globalsportsarchive.com/people/soccer/rylee-traicoff/250313/\n| title          = Laura Su\u00e1rez\n| website        = Global Sports Archive\n| accessdate     = 8 April 2020}}</ref>\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Midfielder]]<ref name=GSA/>\n| currentclub    = [[Puerto Rico Sol]]\n| clubnumber     = 10\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| collegeyears1  = \n| college1       = \n| collegecaps1   = \n| collegegoals1  = \n| years1         = \n| clubs1         = [[Puerto Rico Sol]]\n| caps1          =  \n| goals1         = \n| nationalyears1 = 2011\u20132012\n| nationalteam1  = {{Nwftu|20|Puerto Rico}}\n| nationalcaps1  = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| nationalyears2 = 2014\u2013\n| nationalteam2  = [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico]] \n| nationalcaps2  = 3+\n| nationalgoals2 = 2+\n| pcupdate       = \n| ntupdate       = 7 October 2019\n}}\n{{Spanish name|Su\u00e1rez|Ayala}}\n'''Laura Su\u00e1rez Ayala''' (born 28 July 1992) is a Puerto Rican [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Puerto Rico Sol|Puerto Rico Sol FC]] and the [[Puerto Rico women's national football team|Puerto Rico women's national team]].\n\n==International goals==\n''Scores and results list Puerto Rico's goal tally first.''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! No. !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| <center>1</center> || 19 August 2014 || [[Ato Boldon Stadium]], [[Couva]], [[Trinidad and Tobago]] || {{fbw|JAM}} || <center>'''1'''\u20131</center> || <center>1\u20134</cente